      <P>
        <Text Hanging="indented">This Order brings into force on 30th<Character Name="NonBreakingSpace"/>June 2011 sections<Character Name="NonBreakingSpace"/>1, 5, 7 to 9, 11 to 13, 27, 29(1) and 30 of the Historic Environment (Amendment) (Scotland) Act 2011 (“<Abbreviation Expansion="Historic Environment (Amendment) (Scotland) Act 2011 asp 3">the Act</Abbreviation>”) for all purposes and sections<Character Name="NonBreakingSpace"/>6, 15, 20, 23, 24 and 26 for the limited purposes of enabling the Scottish Ministers to make, or to make provision by means of, subordinate legislation.</Text>
      </P>
      <P>
        <Text Hanging="indented">The Bill for <Abbreviation Expansion="Historic Environment (Amendment) (Scotland) Act 2011 asp 3">the Act</Abbreviation> received Royal Assent on 23rd<Character Name="NonBreakingSpace"/>February 2011. Sections<Character Name="NonBreakingSpace"/>31 to 33 of <Abbreviation Expansion="Historic Environment (Amendment) (Scotland) Act 2011 asp 3">the Act</Abbreviation> came into force the following day.</Text>
      </P>
